---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="Privacy Policy & Terms"
      description="ColorLenz Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. We don't collect your data. Here's the full picture."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <div class="container page-wrap">

        <header class="page-header">
          <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
          <h1>Privacy Policy &amp; Terms</h1>
          <p class="page-intro">
            Short version: we don't collect your data. Here's the long version.
          </p>
          <p class="effective-date">Effective date: May 14, 2026</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose legal-prose">

          <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

          <h3>Overview</h3>
          <p>
            ColorLenz is built on a simple principle: your screen is yours. The app runs
            entirely on your device and does not collect, store, transmit, or share any
            personal information. There is no account system, no analytics, no telemetry.
          </p>

          <h3>What we collect</h3>
          <p>Nothing. ColorLenz does not collect any personal data.</p>
          <p>
            The app operates as a local macOS application. All settings, presets, and
            preferences are stored locally on your device using standard macOS storage
            mechanisms. They never leave your machine.
          </p>

          <h3>Third-party services</h3>
          <p>
            ColorLenz is distributed through the Apple Mac App Store. Apple's own privacy
            practices govern the download and purchase process. You can review Apple's
            privacy policy at <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">apple.com/legal/privacy</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you join the Windows waitlist on our website, we collect your email address
            for the sole purpose of notifying you when the Windows version is available.
            We use a third-party form processor (Formspree) to handle these submissions.
            We will never sell or share your email with anyone. You can request removal
            at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:hello@colorlenz.com">hello@colorlenz.com</a>.
          </p>

          <h3>Cookies &amp; website analytics</h3>
          <p>
            The colorlenz.com website does not use tracking cookies or third-party analytics.
            Standard server logs (IP address, browser type, page visited) may be retained
            briefly by our hosting provider (Cloudflare Pages) in accordance with their
            privacy policy.
          </p>

          <h3>Children's privacy</h3>
          <p>
            ColorLenz does not knowingly collect any information from children under 13.
            As the app collects no data from anyone, this requirement is met by default.
          </p>

          <h3>Changes to this policy</h3>
          <p>
            If we ever change our data practices in a meaningful way, we will update this
            page and the effective date above. We will not make changes that reduce your
            privacy without clear notice.
          </p>

          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>
            Privacy questions? Email us at{' '}
            <a href="mailto:hello@colorlenz.com">hello@colorlenz.com</a>.
          </p>

          <hr />

          <h2>Terms of Use</h2>

          <h3>Acceptance</h3>
          <p>
            By downloading or using ColorLenz, you agree to these terms. If you don't
            agree, please don't use the app.
          </p>

          <h3>License</h3>
          <p>
            ColorLenz grants you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to
            use the application on Apple-branded devices that you own or control, subject
            to the Apple Media Services Terms and Conditions.
          </p>
          <p>You may not:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Copy, modify, or distribute the application</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer or attempt to extract the source code</li>
            <li>Use the application for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Sublicense or sell access to the application</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Disclaimer of warranties</h3>
          <p>
            ColorLenz is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We make no
            representations about the suitability of the app for any particular purpose.
            We do not make any medical claims. ColorLenz is a screen filter tool, not a
            medical device or therapeutic product.
          </p>

          <h3>Limitation of liability</h3>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, ColorLenz and its developers shall
            not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising
            from your use of the application.
          </p>

          <h3>Governing law</h3>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which ColorLenz
            is registered, without regard to conflict of law provisions.
          </p>

          <h3>Changes to terms</h3>
          <p>
            We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the app after
            changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. We'll always post the
            effective date of the most recent version above.
          </p>

          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>
            Questions about these terms? Email us at{' '}
            <a href="mailto:hello@colorlenz.com">hello@colorlenz.com</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .effective-date {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-subtle);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-prose {
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-prose h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-prose p {
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .legal-prose ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-prose li {
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .legal-prose hr {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
</style>
